nodes.text: A Spiced Mynock Wing was a type of food available on the planet Cato Neimoidia sometime between the years 19 and 1 BBY. At one point during that time period, an intoxicated enlisted stormtrooper attempted to eat fifty Spiced Mynock Wings in one sitting, later causing a large mess in a dropship.

Spiced Mynock Wings were first mentioned in "The Infinite Nebstar Casino" entry in the in-game databank of the PlayStation 3/Xbox 360 versions of Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II, a LucasArts video game released in 2010. Spiced Mynock Wings are later mentioned in a short story in Star Wars Insider 146 called "The Syrox Redemption."
